crowdsourced_yara_results.description: Detects malware by known bad imphash or rich_pe_header_hash
crowdsourced_yara_results.author: Arnim Rupp

threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The binary is a position-independent shellcode loader. It dynamically resolves API functions by walking the PEB, locating loaded modules, and hashing exported function names using a `ror 13` algorithm. The presence of the obfuscated string "ws2_32" indicates an intent to load the Winsock library for networking capabilities. It allocates executable memory via `VirtualAlloc` and jumps to it, a classic technique for executing a second-stage payload.
